Here C is the effective number of suns imposed by the IR bias light, and IAM1.5G is the solar irradiance of the AM1.5G reference solar spectrum in units of W m−1 nm−1 from the National Renewable Energy Laboratory. By using SI units for all the physical constants on the right-hand side of the equation, the current density in units of mA cm−2 can be approximated in a discretized form as:ΔJsc=8×10−5⋅Δλ∑i=1NIAM1.5GλiΔEQEiλi\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
